                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.515/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-18T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 18, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Your 62, March 8, 10 a.m. For McBride. The Treasury and War Departments are
                    in consultation regarding the currency problem and expect to furnish us with a
                    definite reply to your recommendation in the near future. It is probable that
                    your suggestions will in large measure be adopted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
